metadata.name: Tesseract #362
metadata.description:
'Tesseract' is a generative collection drawing on the concept of the cube from oneirology, the interpretation of dreams. In many mythologies and fields of study, the square is considered a 'perfect shape', thus with its abstraction into three isometric dimensions, the cube is seen by some as a representation of the various aspects of the human condition.

In 'Tesseract', the ribbons flowing between the cubes represent the shared experiences that connect us all. No matter how different our lives might be, we all go through the same joys, sorrows, trials, tribulations and experience attachments of varying degrees. 

It is these experiences that bind us together and make us who we are. With these concepts in mind, viewers are invited to interpret each composition as it relates to them and their unique story, from the perspective of that which has been and that which is yet to be experienced.

Press 'S' to save a high resolution PNG at 2400 x 3396 px.

metadata.name: Altered #195
metadata.description:
Adj. Changed in character or composition, typically in a comparatively small but significant way.

Please note that the display is progressive and can take some time to finalize.

Artwork by Patrice Orenes-Lerma - @patxol - 2022
Made with math, love & p5js.
CC BY-SA 4.0 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

Features include :

- 20 color palettes (10 standard, 10 rare)
- 8 palette progression types
- 3 aspect ratio (Portrait is standard, 1:1 and landscape are rare)
- 8 Alteration types
- 3 Alteration power levels
- 5 types of symmetry
- 3 densities
- Spaced mode and Sharp mode

metadata.name: Balanced #105
metadata.description:
What does balance look like when viewed through the lens of pure mathematics? This is the question Balanced attempts to answer.

Each output is composed of a unique collection of blocks mathematically stacked to be in perfect balance.

This is my Genesis project. Enjoy!

Interactions:
1 - Reverse your stack vertically and re-balance.
2 - Toggle between square and portrait frame.
3 - Show center of mass. 
4 - Toggle the border.
5 - Toggle the background (color/transparent)
6 - Export image (2048x2048)
7 - Export image (4096x4096)
8 - Export image (8192x8192)

How it was made: https://www.jeffweber.art/balanced

metadata.name: GE-I #447
metadata.description:
The first in a series of grid experiments.

Made of simple expressions of shape, color, and layout. There are 10 features including 32 pallets & 34 shape sets. The base grid is constructed of either 2x2, 4x4, 6x6, 8x8, or 20x20 layouts.

metadata.name: Tree Rings #162
metadata.description:
Experimenting with organic movement. Each ring is meant to show the differing growth patterns the tree may have from year to year and what sort of nutrients it's received.

Each Tree Ring has 1 - 9 rings, with 200 - 1000 radians, each ring and background selected from a library of 64 colors.
